article.headline: Sam Houston outplays Wisconsin-Milwaukee for win
article.linkText: Sam Houston outplays Wisconsin-Milwaukee for win
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Texas (AP) -- James Barrett scored 27 points to lead Sam Houston State to an 89-73 win over Wisconsin-Milwaukee on Friday night. Barrett, who played 20 minutes, also had seven rebounds and three blocks. He made nine-of-13 field goals and all three 3-point attempts. Ryan Bright finished with 11 points, six rebounds three assists and two blocks for Sam Houston State (7-5). Aaron Wade came off the bench to score 15 points and grab eight rebounds in 18 minutes. The Bearkats shot 58 percent on 3-pointers, led by Barrett and Wade, who was 4-of-4 from beyond the arc. Avery Smith led the Panthers (2-11) with 18 points. Allan Hanson scored 10. The Bearkats never trailed, jumping out to a 19-9 lead to open the game.
